  "bib_entries": {
    "119346490": {
      "title": "On the couplings of the rho meson in AdS/QCD",
      "abstract": "/f . The argument relies upon the fact that the ρ is the lowest-lying state created by a conserved current, and the detailed form of the integrals which determinethe couplings in AdS/QCD. Quasi-universality holds even when rho-dominance is violated. Theargument fails for all other hadrons, except for the lowest-lying spin-two hadron created by theenergy-momentum tensor. Explicit examples are discussed."
    }
